<para id="element-46">If we ponder a bit, then we would realize that when we deal with component speed or magnitude of component velocity then we are essentially dealing with unidirectional motion. No change in direction is possible as components are aligned to a fixed axis. As such, equating rate of change in speed with the magnitude of acceleration in component direction is valid. Now, proceeding ahead,
